categories.name: Binary Exploitation
categories.description: Buffer overflows, ROP, and binary exploitation

challenges.title: SQL Injection Basics
challenges.description: Exploit a simple SQL injection vulnerability to retrieve the admin password. The login form is vulnerable to basic SQL injection attacks. Try using `' OR '1'='1` to bypass authentication.

challenges.title: XSS Playground
challenges.description: Find and exploit a Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability. The comment section doesn't properly sanitize user input. Can you execute JavaScript in another user's browser?

challenges.title: CSRF Token Bypass
challenges.description: Exploit a Cross-Site Request Forgery vulnerability. The application has CSRF protection but it's implemented incorrectly. Find the flaw and exploit it.

challenges.title: JWT Secret Cracking
challenges.description: The application uses JWT tokens with a weak secret. Crack the secret and forge an admin token. The secret is a common English word.

challenges.title: Server-Side Template Injection
challenges.description: Find and exploit a Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI) vulnerability. The template engine executes user input without proper sanitization. Get remote code execution!

challenges.title: Caesar Cipher
challenges.description: Decrypt this message encrypted with a simple Caesar cipher: `FWI{fdhvdu_flskhu_lv_wrr_hdvb}`. The shift is 3.

challenges.title: Base64 Encoding
challenges.description: Decode this Base64 encoded flag: `Q1RGe2I0czY0X2lzX25vdF9lbmNyeXB0aW9ufQ==`

challenges.title: RSA Small Exponent
challenges.description: The RSA implementation uses e=3 with a small message. Use the small exponent attack to recover the plaintext. n = 0x9b3f..., c = 0x1234...

challenges.title: AES ECB Mode Weakness
challenges.description: Exploit the weakness of AES in ECB mode. The server encrypts user input and returns the ciphertext. Use the ECB penguin attack to leak information.

challenges.title: Padding Oracle Attack
challenges.description: Exploit a padding oracle vulnerability in CBC mode encryption. The server reveals whether padding is valid. Use this to decrypt the ciphertext byte by byte.

challenges.title: Hidden EXIF Data
challenges.description: Download the image and examine the EXIF metadata. The flag is hidden in the GPS coordinates field.

challenges.title: Deleted Files Recovery
challenges.description: A file was deleted from this disk image. Use forensic tools to recover it. The flag is in the recovered file.

challenges.title: Memory Dump Analysis
challenges.description: Analyze this memory dump from a compromised system. The attacker's password is stored in plaintext in memory. Use volatility to find it.

challenges.title: Network Traffic Analysis
challenges.description: Analyze the PCAP file to find the flag. An attacker exfiltrated data using DNS tunneling. Decode the DNS queries to get the flag.

challenges.title: Steganography in Audio
challenges.description: The flag is hidden in this audio file using LSB steganography. Extract the hidden data from the least significant bits.

challenges.title: Buffer Overflow 101
challenges.description: Exploit a simple buffer overflow to overwrite the return address. The binary has no protections (NX disabled, no ASLR, no PIE).

challenges.title: Format String Vulnerability
challenges.description: Exploit a format string vulnerability to leak stack data. Use %x and %s format specifiers to read memory.

challenges.title: Return-Oriented Programming
challenges.description: Chain ROP gadgets to bypass NX protection and get a shell. The binary has NX enabled but no ASLR. Gadgets are available in libc.

challenges.title: Heap Overflow Exploitation
challenges.description: Exploit a heap overflow vulnerability to overwrite function pointers. The binary uses malloc/free without proper bounds checking.

challenges.title: Simple Crack Me
challenges.description: Reverse engineer this binary to find the correct password. The password checking logic is straightforward with simple comparisons.

challenges.title: String Obfuscation
challenges.description: The flag is obfuscated using XOR encoding. Reverse the algorithm and decode the flag. The XOR key is 0x42.

challenges.title: Anti-Debugging Tricks
challenges.description: This binary uses anti-debugging techniques. Bypass the debugger detection to find the flag. Use patching or emulation.

challenges.title: VM-Based Obfuscation
challenges.description: The binary implements a custom virtual machine to obfuscate the flag checking logic. Reverse the VM instructions to find the flag.

challenges.title: Malware Analysis
challenges.description: Analyze this malware sample to extract the C2 server address. The address is encrypted with a custom algorithm. WARNING: Run in a sandboxed environment!
